apt-blitz (0.5.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Adaptive worker pool: start with min(connections, 4) workers,
    scale up on successful segments, degrade gracefully on failures.
  * Download no longer aborts on first worker error; fails only
    when all workers are dead and buffer is incomplete.

 -- Petr Sleptsov <spetr@bk.ru>  Tue, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0300

apt-blitz (0.4.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add per-stream read timeout (30s) with automatic retry on hang.
  * Validate segment volume after download; retry on mismatch.
  * Handle HTTP 200 instead of 206: truncate writes to segment boundary.
  * Add connect_timeout(10s) and overall timeout(300s) to reqwest client.
  * Warn on Content-Length vs range mismatch in 206 responses.

 -- Petr Sleptsov <spetr@bk.ru>  Tue, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0300

apt-blitz (0.4.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix is_transient_error to cover Decode and Request error kinds,
    enabling proper retries for body stream and request send failures.
  * Fix FailureTracker race by moving cooldown check into
    resolve_with_coalescing retry loop.
  * Fix claim_range(0) infinite loop by returning None for zero-size claims.

 -- Petr Sleptsov <spetr@bk.ru>  Tue, 14 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0300

apt-blitz (0.4.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add segment-level retry with exponential backoff for transient network errors.
  * Add per-URL failure cooldown (3 failures / 60s) to prevent retry storms.
  * Add Coalescer::fail() for explicit failure notification to followers.

 -- Petr Sleptsov <spetr@bk.ru>  Tue, 14 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0300

apt-blitz (0.4.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add request tracing with per-request ID and spans.

